my meme:

my meme was based on a cat hiding in the blanket avoiding an email that it had been sent. i have re created the meme by changing the picture and adding in another picture and another part to the meme.i also changed some details like colors and fonts.

code for my meme:

library(magick)

#top words
writing_square <- image_blank(width = 400, height = 35, color = "#008fad") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "I hope this email finds you well", color = "#000000", size = 30, font = "serif",gravity = "north")

#first picture (on the left)
picture_square <- image_read("cat_on_computer.jpeg") %>%
  image_crop("200x200", gravity = "north") %>%
  image_annotate(text = " how the email found me: ", color = "#000000", size = 18, font = "serif", gravity = "south", boxcolor = "#008fad")

#second picture (on the right)
picture_square_2 <- image_read("cat_attack.jpeg") %>%
  image_resize("200x200!") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "    how i read the email:    ", color = "#000000", size = 18, font = "serif", gravity = "south", boxcolor = "#008fad")

#combining all togther
pictures <- c(picture_square, picture_square_2)
picture_3 <- image_append(pictures)
frames <- c(writing_square, picture_3)
new_meme <- image_append(frames, stack = TRUE)

#saving the meme
image_write(new_meme, "my_meme.png")

my animation:

my animation is a skater going though a sequence of movments. i am an roller skater (like ice bit slightly different), i have chosen an ice figure skater whos silhouette changes thoughout the gif as it shows the beauty of skating. it also moves closer and further away thought the gif to give the illusion of the skater moving on the ice. the start is the skater already skating, and she contiues to flows though her movments and she finshes in a final ending position.

code for my animation:

library(magick)

#first image-good
first_pic <- image_read("animation_1.1.png") %>%
  image_scale("200")

#sceond imgae -grey
second_pic <- image_read("animation_2.2.png") %>%
  image_scale("200")


#third image -good
third_pic <- image_read("animation_1.5.png") %>%
  image_scale("200")


#foruth image - grey
fourth_pic <- image_read("animation_1.2.png") %>%
  image_scale("200")

#fith image-grey
fith_pic <- image_read("anitmation_5.png") %>%
  image_scale("200")

#sixth image- good
sixth_pic <- image_read("animation_1.4.png") %>%
  image_scale("200")


#seven pic needs fixing
seven_pic <- image_read("animation_2.1.png") %>%
  image_scale("200")


#eigth pic -good
eight_pic <- image_read("animation_1.6.png") %>%
  image_scale("200")


animation <- c(second_pic, third_pic, sixth_pic, seven_pic, eight_pic, first_pic)%>%
  image_animate(fps = 1)


#svaing the gif
image_write(animation, "my_anitmation.gif")
